---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
// Account-deletion page — the public web URL required by Google Play for apps
// with account creation. In-app deletion is the primary path (Account ->
// Delete my account; server DELETE /user/me, Story 10.1). This page gives the
// web-accessible instructions + an email fallback. Plain, compliance-clear
// voice (Handler's Brief: no hype). Design matches the landing (Base + brand).
---

<Base
  title="Delete your account — Survive the Talk"
  description="How to permanently delete your Survive the Talk account and all your data."
>
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section aria-labelledby="delete-title">
      <div class="mx-0 max-w-[720px] px-6 pt-10 pb-16 md:pl-20 md:pr-8 md:pt-16 md:pb-24">
        <h1
          id="delete-title"
          class="font-display text-[clamp(28px,6vw,64px)] uppercase leading-none text-text-primary"
        >
          Delete your account
        </h1>

        <p class="mt-6 max-w-[62ch] text-body text-text-primary">
          You can permanently delete your Survive the Talk account and all the
          data tied to it, in one step. Here is how.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-10 text-headline text-text-primary">In the app (instant)</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 max-w-[62ch] text-body text-text-primary">
          Open <span class="font-medium">Survive the Talk</span> →
          <span class="font-medium">Account</span> →
          <span class="font-medium">Delete my account</span>, then confirm. This
          permanently removes your email, your call history, your debrief
          summaries, your progress, and your subscription records — in one
          operation. It cannot be undone.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-8 text-headline text-text-primary">By email</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 max-w-[62ch] text-body text-text-primary">
          If you cannot open the app, email
          <a
            href="mailto:contact@survivethetalk.com?subject=Delete%20my%20account"
            class="text-text-primary underline underline-offset-2"
            >contact@survivethetalk.com</a
          >
          from your account's email address and ask us to delete your account.
          We remove it within 30 days.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-8 text-headline text-text-primary">If you have a subscription</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 max-w-[62ch] text-body text-text-primary">
          Deleting your account does <span class="font-medium">not</span> cancel
          a paid subscription — Google Play and Apple manage subscriptions, not
          us. To stop auto-renewal, also cancel it in your store:
          <span class="font-medium">Google Play → Subscriptions</span> (or
          <span class="font-medium">App Store → Subscriptions</span>).
        </p>

        <p class="mt-8 max-w-[62ch] text-caption text-text-secondary">
          Your voice is never stored — it is processed live during a call and
          discarded — so there is nothing to delete there. Full details are in
          the
          <a
            href="https://survivethetalk.com/legal/privacy"
            class="underline underline-offset-2">Privacy Policy</a
          >.
        </p>

        <a
          href="/"
          class="mt-9 inline-block text-caption text-text-secondary underline underline-offset-2"
        >
          Back to the start
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
